The '''mean time between coincidences''' ('''MTBC''') is used in [[safety engineering]] and is defined as the reciprocal of the average frequency of dangerous [[coincidence]]s:

<math>MTBC=\frac{1}{\lambda\ _{d}} = \frac{2}{\lambda\ \mu\ \tau\ }</math>

